{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2014}} {{Use Indian English|date=October 2014}} '''Radio Gold''' is a radio channel of [[All India Radio]].<ref>[http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2010-11-05/india/28238416_1_new-frequency-fm-gold-mhz-band No shifting FM Gold, old frequency stays]. The Times of India. 5 November 2010.</ref> It is aired in [[Delhi]], [[Mumbai]], [[Indore]], [[Kolkata]], and [[Chennai]].
The 106.4 FM Radio Gold also started its transmission in other centres of Tamil Nadu like [[Coimbatore]], [[Tuticorin]] and more recently, in [[Puducherry]].
