{{Infobox Union |name= |country= [[Bangladesh]] |affiliation= [[World Federation of Trade Unions|WFTU]] |members= |full_name= Bangladesh Jatiyo Sramik Jote |native_name= |image= |founded= |current= |head= |dissolved_date= |dissolved_state= |merged_into= |office= [[Dhaka]], Bangladesh |people= |website= [http://jatiyosramikjote.org jatiyosramikjote.org] |footnotes= }} <!-- Include all unused fields for future use. See [[template talk:Infobox Union]] for usage. -->
The '''Bangladesh Jatiyo Sarmik Jote''' ([[translation]]: ''Bangladesh National Workers Front'') is a national [[trade union]] federation in [[Bangladesh]]. It is affiliated with the [[World Federation of Trade Unions]].
BJSJ is politically tied to the [[Jatiyo Samajtantrik Dal]] (JSD).
