{{Infobox election | election_name = Cape Verdean parliamentary election, 2006 | country = Cape Verde | type = parliamentary | ongoing = no | colours = yes | previous_election = Cape Verdean parliamentary election, 2001 | previous_year = 2001 | next_election = Cape Verdean parliamentary election, 2011 | next_year = 2011 | election_date = 22 January 2006 | registered = 322.725 | opinion_polls = | turnout = 54.18% | image1 = [[File:Jm neves.jpg|115px]] | leader1 = [[José Maria Neves]] | party1 = African Party for the Independence of Cape Verde | popular_vote1 = 88,965 | percentage1 = 52.28% | seats1 = 41 | seat_change1 = {{increase}} 1 | image2 = [[File:no image.svg]] | leader2 = [[Carlos Veiga]] | party2 = Movement for Democracy (Cape Verde) | popular_vote2 = 74,909 | percentage2 = 44.02% | seats2 = 29 | seat_change2 = {{decrease}} 1 | colour3 = 128385 | image3 = [[File:No image.png|115px]] | leader3 = [[João dos Santos Luís]] | party3 = [[Democratic and Independent Cape Verdean Union|UCID]] | popular_vote3 = 4,495 | percentage3 = 2.64% | seats3 = 2 | seat_change3 = {{steady}} | title = [[Prime Minister of Cape Verde|Prime Minister]] | before_election = [[José Maria Neves]] | before_party = African Party for the Independence of Cape Verde | after_election = [[José Maria Neves]] | after_party = African Party for the Independence of Cape Verde }} [[File:Asamblea Nacional de Cabo Verde de 2006.svg|thumb|right|350px|Seats of the National Assembly after the 2006 parliamentary election]] {{Politics of Cape Verde}}
'''Parliamentary elections''' were held in [[Cape Verde]] on 22 January 2006. The result was a victory for the ruling [[African Party for the Independence of Cape Verde]] (PAICV) run by [[José Maria Neves]], which won 41 of the 72 seats in the [[National Assembly (Cape Verde)|National Assembly]].<ref>[http://africanelections.tripod.com/cv.html Elections in Cape Verde] African Elections Database</ref> Second was the [[Movement for Democracy (Cape Verde)|Movement for Democracy]] (Mpd) and third was [[Democratic and Independent Cape Verdean Union]] (UCID) led by João Santos dos Luís.
==Campaign== The PAICV and the MpD (led by [[Ulisses Correia e Silva]]) were the only parties to nominate a candidate in every constituency.
