{{Infobox journal | title = Development and Change | cover = | editor = Ashwani Saith, Murat Arsel, Kees Biekart, Amrita Chhachhi, Bridget O'Laughlin, Servaas Storm | discipline = [[Development studies]], [[Social change]] | former_names = | abbreviation = Dev. Change | publisher = [[Wiley-Blackwell]] on behalf of the [[Institute of Social Studies]]. | country = | frequency = Bimonthly | history = 1970-present | openaccess = | license = | impact = 1.411 | impact-year = 2011 | website = http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/journal/10.1111/(ISSN)1467-7660 | link1 = http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/journal/10.1111/(ISSN)1467-7660/currentissue | link1-name = Online access | link2 = http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/journal/10.1111/(ISSN)1467-7660/issues | link2-name = Online archive | JSTOR = | OCLC = 781557999 | LCCN = 76018510 | CODEN = | ISSN = 0012-155X | eISSN = 1467-7660 }} '''''Development and Change''''' is a bimonthly [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] published by [[Wiley-Blackwell]] on behalf of the [[Institute of Social Studies]]. The journal was established in 1970 and covers [[development studies]] and [[social change]]. Specific topics of interest are international agencies, macroanalysis, [[non-governmental organization]]s, [[public policy]], [[social structure]], and [[sustainability]]. According to the ''[[Journal Citation Reports]]'', the journal has a 2011 [[impact factor]] of 1.411, ranking it 15th out of 54 journals in the category "Planning and Development".<ref name=WoS>{{cite book |year=2012 |chapter=Journals Ranked by Impact: Planning and Development |title=2011 [[Journal Citation Reports]] |publisher=[[Thomson Reuters]] |edition=Social Sciences |accessdate=2012-11-16 |series=Web of Science |postscript=.}}</ref>
