{{Infobox university | name = Jean Lorougnon Guédé University | native_name = Université Jean Lorougnon Guédé | image_name = | image_size = | image_alt = | caption = | latin_name = | motto = | mottoeng = | established = {{Start date|1996}} | closed = | type = [[Public university|Public]] | affiliation = | endowment = | officer_in_charge = | chairman = | chancellor = | president = [[Gnakri Dago]] | vice-president = | superintendent = | provost = | vice_chancellor = | rector = | principal = | dean = | director = | head_label = [[Visitor]] | head = | academic_staff = | administrative_staff = 144 | students = 2,000 | undergrad = | postgrad = | doctoral = | other = | city = [[Daloa]] | state = | province = | country = [[Côte d'Ivoire]] | coor = | campus = [[Rural area|Rural]] | former_names = | free_label = | free = | colors = | colours = | athletics = | sports = | nickname = | mascot = | affiliations = [[Agence universitaire de la Francophonie|AUF]] | website = {{URL|www.ujlog.ci}} | logo = | footnotes = }} '''Jean Lorougnon Guédé University''' (in French ''Université Jean-Lorougnon-Guédé'') is an [[Côte d'Ivoire|Ivorian]] public university located in [[Daloa]], in the west central region of [[Côte d'Ivoire]]. Jean Lorougnon Guédé is member of several organizations of higher education, in particular the French-speaking University Agency ([[Agence universitaire de la Francophonie|AUF]])<ref>{{cite web|language=french |url=http://www.auf.org/membres/1350/?height=602&width=604 |title=Université Jean Lorougnon Guédé|website=auf.org |author=|date= |accessdate=13 October 2014}}</ref> and the Telecoms research and education network of Côte d'Ivoire.
==History==
Originally the school was a detachment of the University of Abobo-Adjamé. It has been a full-function university since 1996.
