{{Orphan|date=August 2015}}
The ''' Justices of the Supreme Court of Nigeria''' are members of the [[Supreme Court of Nigeria]] headed by the [[Chief Justice of Nigeria]]. The Justices are often recommended by the [[National Judicial Council (Nigeria)|National Judicial Council]] to the [[President of Nigeria]], who will send the names to the [[Senate (Nigeria)|Senate]] for confirmation.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thenationonlineng.net/2011/index.php/news/23532-senate-confirms-justice-ariwoola-for-supreme-court.html|title=Senate confirms Justice Ariwoola for Supreme Court|work=The Nation|accessdate=1 April 2015}}</ref> Currently, there are 16 Justices of the Supreme court of Nigeria, including the Chief Justice of Nigeria. Prior to the appointment of Justice Olukayode Ariwola and Mary Odili, the wife of [[Peter Odili]], there were 14 Justices of the Supreme Court, including the Chief Justice of Nigeria.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://supremecourt.gov.ng/|title=Supreme Court of Nigeria|work=supremcourt.gov.ng|accessdate=1 April 2015}}
==Current Justices== *[[Mahmud Mohammed]] *[[Ibrahim Tanko Muhammad]] *[[Muntaka Connmassie]] *[[Bode Rhodes-Vivour]] *[[Suleiman Galadima]] *[[John Afolabi Fabiyi]] *[[Mary Odili]] *[[Nwali Sylvester Ngwuta]] *[[Olukayode Ariwoola]] *[[Musa Datijo Muhammad]] *[[Kumai Bayang Akaahs]] *[[Clara Bata Ogunbiyi]] *[[Kudirat Motonmori Olatokunbo]] *[[Chima Centus Nweze]] *[[John Inyang Okoro]] *[[Walter Samuel Nkanu Onnoghen]]
