{{short description|1984 Czechoslovakian film directed by Miroslav Luther}} {{unreliable sources|date=October 2018}} {{Use mdy dates|date=April 2016}} {{Infobox film | name = King Thrushbeard | image = | alt = | caption = | director = Miroslav Luther | producer = | screenplay = | based on = [[Grimm Brothers]] fairy-tale ''[[King Thrushbeard|Red Beard]]'' | starring = Adriana Tarábková, Lukás Vaculík, Maria Schell | music = | cinematography = | editing = | studio = [[ZDF]] | distributor = Omnia-Film München, Slovenská filmová tvorba Bratislava | released = 1984 | runtime = | country = Czechoslovakia (now Slovakia) & Germany | language = Slovak and German | budget = | gross = }}
'''''King Thrushbeard''''' (film) is a 1984 Czechoslovakian film based on an adaptation of the [[Grimm Brothers]] fairy-tale ''[[King Thrushbeard|Red Beard]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.sky.com/tv/movie/king-thrushbeard-1984 |title= King Thrushbeard |work= Sky|accessdate=October 23, 2018}}</ref> (originally known in [[German language|German]] as ''König Drosselbart'' and in [[Slovak language|Slovak]] as ''Král Drozdia Brada'')
==Plot== A fairy-tale about a beautiful but very haughty princess Anna who cruelly mocks each of her suitors. Finally, she is forced by the king to marry a beggar. The poor life, hard work, and love teach the princess a lesson and turn her into a loving and kind person.{{Citation needed|date=October 2018}}
