{{Infobox Airline |airline = Kivu Air |logo = |logo_size = |fleet_size = 1 |destinations = |IATA = - |ICAO = - |callsign = - |parent = |company_slogan = |founded = 1997 |headquarters = [[Goma]], [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]] |key_people = |hubs = [[Goma International Airport]], [[Bukavu Airport]] |secondary_hubs = |focus_cities = |frequent_flyer = |lounge = |alliance = |website = }}
'''Kivu Air''' is an [[airline]] based in [[Goma]], [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]]. It operates charter and cargo services in the area. Its main bases are [[Goma International Airport]] and [[Bukavu Airport]].<ref name="FI">{{cite news | title= Directory: World Airlines | work= [[Flight International]] | page= 101 | date= 2007-04-03}}</ref>
The airline is on the [[List of air carriers banned in the European Union]].
== History == The airline was established and started operations in 1997. It has 27 employees (at March 2007).<ref name="FI"/>
