The '''National Alliance for Progress''' ({{lang-fr|Alliance Nationale pour le Progrès, ANP}}) is a [[political party]] in [[Guinea]]. In the [[Guinean parliamentary election, 2002|parliamentary election]] held on 30 June 2002, the party won 2% of the popular vote and 2 out of 114 seats.<ref name='African Elections Database'> {{cite web|url=http://africanelections.tripod.com/gn.html |title=Elections in Guinea |accessdate=2007-02-24 }}</ref>

